            "href": "/study/general-conference/2018/10/the-correct-name-of-the-church?lang=eng&amp;para=16#p16",
            "text": "The Correct Name of the Church",
            "type": "cross-ref"
          }
        ]
      },
      "note19": {
        "marker": "19.",
        "pid": "149808497",
        "id": "note19",
        "text": "<p data-aid=\"149808776\" id=\"note19_p1\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/nt/matt/18.6?lang=eng#p6\">Matthew 18:6<\/a>. \u201cThe terrible, vicious practice of sexual abuse \u2026 is beyond understanding. \u2026 It is a violation of that which is sacred and divine. \u2026 It is reprehensible and worthy of the most severe condemnation. Shame on any man or woman who would sexually abuse a child. In doing so, the abuser not only does the most serious kind of injury. He or she also stands condemned before the Lord\u201d (Gordon B. Hinckley, \u201c<a class=\"cross-ref\" href=\"/study/general-conference/1994/10/save-the-children?lang=eng&amp;para=39#p39\">Save the Children<\/a>,\u201d <cite>Ensign<\/cite>, Nov. 1994, 54).<\/p>",
